<subSubSection id="F3BDCE40C590566A57D8EDD0AB3DD2F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="023049123A6E7F7C41A0FEFB6FE70AEF" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="42764215AF2073425200419DA5A5EA29" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Twining perennial liana to 3 m; stems woody, grey, glabrous. Leaves borne on brachyblasts, sometimes clustered, petiolate, palmately divided into 5-7 leaflets, leaflets 1-2.5 
<normalizedToken id="466A4AAEFD156A039CA56CF6BE8B5ED8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.05-0.7 cm, linear, oblong, oblanceolate to obovate, obtuse or retuse, tapered at base into petiole, paler and punctate beneath, glabrous; petioles 1.5-3.5 cm. Flowers solitary or paired,
<normalizedToken id="454B28E9028A00D106F694E7338ABCDF" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
terminal from the brachyblasts; peduncle very short, 1-2 mm; bracteoles caducous; pedicels 6-14 mm; sepals unequal, glabrous with broad scarious margins, outer 4-5 
<normalizedToken id="1BA2DB063A2CC68DECBF0A47E1D37055" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3-4 mm, elliptic to suborbicular, inner c. 7 
<normalizedToken id="B71926C5B412A77EB4F2B23BCFE7A8D2" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
4-5 mm, elliptic, obtuse; corolla 3-3.5 cm long, narrowly funnel-shaped, glabrous, tube greenish, limb pale pink, 2-2.5 cm diam.; stamens held at corolla mouth. Capsules ovoid, rostrate, glabrous; seeds long pilose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
